          - mLabel: Metallic
            mType: Property
            mName: metallicFactor
            mWidget: slider
            mHint: |-
              Property: metallicFactor
              
              1 means metal, 0 means non-metal (dielectric). Multiplies the metallic channel of the Material Params texture if enabled.
            mMin: 0.000000
            mMax: 1.000000
            mStep: 0.010000
            mDefaultVal: 1.000000
            mValues:
              []
          - mLabel: Roughness
            mType: Property
            mName: roughnessFactor
            mWidget: slider
            mHint: |-
              Property: roughnessFactor
              
              1 means completely rough (diffuse), 0 means perfectly smooth and shiny.  Multiplies the roughness channel of the Material Params texture if enabled.  If your roughness is 1 and your metallic is 0, it's more efficient to disable Specular alltogether.
            mMin: 0.000000
            mMax: 1.000000
            mStep: 0.010000
            mDefaultVal: 1.000000
            mValues:
              []
          - mLabel: Metallic-Roughness Texture
            mType: Define
            mName: ENABLE_METALLIC_ROUGHNESS_TEX
            mWidget: group_start
            mHint: |-
              Define: ENABLE_METALLIC_ROUGHNESS_TEX
              
              If enabled, it multiplies each channel with the Metallic, Roughness and Occlusion factor.
            mMin: ~
            mMax: ~
            mStep: ~
            mDefaultVal: ~
            mValues:
              []
          - mLabel: Occlusion Strength
            mType: Property
            mName: occlusionTextureStrength
            mWidget: slider
            mHint: |-
              Property: occlusionTextureStrength
              
              1 means full indirect lighting, 0 means no indirect lighting. Multiplies the occlusion channel of the Material Params texture if enabled.
